summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVegane.l.f. Cosmetics 16HR Camo Concealer is a crease-proof liquid concealer that provides 16-hour full coverage and a matte finish while moisturizing your skin.
details: DetailsBenefitsFull coverage liquid concealer with a smooth, matte finish and long 16-hour wear timeLarge doe foot applicator offers easy, even, and precise applicationLightweight, highly pigmented formula won't settle into fine lines or creasesIngredient-driven formula moisturizes skin, while helping control shineUse to conceal, correct, contour and highlightFor normal, combination, and oily skinAvailable in 26 shades100% vegan, cruelty-free, and Leaping Bunny Certified.Key IngredientsAvocado Oil - Moisturizes and protects skinKaolin Clay - Helps control excess oil and shineFormulated WithoutPhthalatesParabensNonylphenol EthoxylatesTriclosanTriclocarbanHydroquinoneItem 2538873How To Use‚Ä¢ Prep the under-eye area with the e.l.f. Holy Hydration! Eye Cream followed by the Poreless Putty Primer on top. ‚Ä¢ Use the doefoot applicator to apply concealer to desired areas. ‚Ä¢ Blend concealer with using the Flawless Concealer Brush by stippling areas that needed heavier coverage and buffing out the remainder. ‚Ä¢ Fingers or a sponge can be used as an alternate to blend the concealer.IngredientsWater (Aqua), Cyclopentasiloxane, Acrylates Crosspolymer, Butylene Glycol, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Sodium Chloride, Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Oil, Kaolin, Silica, Dimethicone, Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Acrylates/Dimethicone Copolymer, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Caprylyl Glycol, Disodium EDTA, Ethylhexylglycerin, Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).
how_to_use: ‚Ä¢ Prep the under-eye area with the e.l.f. Holy Hydration! Eye Cream followed by the Poreless Putty Primer on top. ‚Ä¢ Use the doefoot applicator to apply concealer to desired areas. ‚Ä¢ Blend concealer with using the Flawless Concealer Brush by stippling areas that needed heavier coverage and buffing out the remainder. ‚Ä¢ Fingers or a sponge can be used as an alternate to blend the concealer.

faceoff_positive.comments: I've struggled with finding an elf concealer that is fair enough to use under my eyes, so I bought the lightest warm shade in the collection. To my surprise, it was significantly lighter than the lightest shade of the HD Lifting Concealer! I ended up loving the formula, so I repurchased the camo concealer in the shade medium peach, which is a much better match. I hope these swatches are useful...for reference, I am shade 110 porcelain in Maybelline smooth and dewy foundation and Shell Ivory in the Wet 'n Wild photofocus foundation.
faceoff_positive.headline: Good color range for fair skin

faceoff_negative.comments:
I was SO excited to try this concealer as it seems to be all the rage on the YT beauty channels. And YES...it covers/ conceals, it IS blendable (if you work SUPER fast as it is very fast setting), it DOES last (I have not tried the full 16 hours, but last longer than some others I have tried) BUT...it also enhances every.single. fine line. under my eyes. EVERY one, even the ones I didn't know I had until I used this product.

My skin is normal and well hydrated. No other concealer I have used has placed a spotlight on my fine lines like this does.

What I have tried (using only 2 little dots, not the entire applicator fill)

*Using alone over my normal hydration

*Adding extra hydration

*Adding hydration TO the concealer

Application:

*Using my finger

*Using a concealer brush

*Using a flat foundation brush

*Using a Beauty Blender

NOTHING helps. 

Love SO many of the E.L.F. products, but for this one I am not a fan.
faceoff_negative.headline: it covers, it blends, it lasts BUT...
